                            <comment id="17775102" author="JIRAUSER302569" created="Sat, 14 Oct 2023 01:18:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed the packaging/src/docker/conf/hive-site.xml file.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13063548/13063548_image-2023-10-14-09-17-47-281.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38107489/274453312-45bd5973-8bab-489f-9304-d1bc40a36661.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I discovered this bug when using it. Since the default directory does not exist for non-root users in the container, it caused an error message without permission to create databases and data tables. After that, I corrected hive.metastore.warehouse.dir, this configuration item by rebuilding the image. This bug is solved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct related configuration items are in the picture below.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/38107489/274453045-880ced5c-fd72-43b6-abc0-da1735a0bfb1.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
